Md Romel Sharif, CAMS, CCI is an ACAMS-certified anti-financial crime specialist with over 16 years of experience in internal audit, compliance, and financial crime risk management. He has led multiple regulatory audits and compliance reviews across banks, fintechs, and Money Services Businesses (MSBs), with expertise in AML/CFT governance, sanctions compliance, fraud risk assessment, and regulatory reporting.

As a recognized thought leader in the compliance community, he has contributed to industry publications, conducted specialized training for compliance officers, and been nominated for awards such as ACAMS Today “Article of the Year” 2025. His work focuses on empowering auditors and compliance professionals with practical, risk-based methodologies to uphold financial integrity and regulatory accountability.
